### Typess decllaration instruction: 

        the instruction is used to declare the type of variable being used in the program
        likw what are the correct instructions to declare a variable
        int a, b, C ; int a = 10; int a, b, c ; a =b= c= 10; 
        float p, q, r 
        char name, roll_no

Note: modular operator is (%) not used with float type or variable.
      also the remained we get usign modular symbol ( % ) the sign is same as in the numerator of the problem 
      ex: -10 % 2 = -5, whereas 10 % 2 = 5 so whatever the sign of numerator is comes with the output remainder
      

Arithmatic instructions:

        instructions consist of a varibale name on the left side of the '=' and the constants are on the right side of the '=' and variable and constants are connected with operators are called arithmatic instructions.
        ex-> 
            int ad;
            float kot, deta, alpha, beta, gamma; 
            ad = 3200;
            kot = 0.0056;
            deta = alpha * beta / gamma + 3.2 * 2 / 5;

            here:   * / + - are the operators 
                    = is an assignment operator 
                    2, 5, 3200 are the integer constants.
                    0.0056, 3.2 are the real constants decimal values.
                    rest, ad, kot, alpha, beta, gamma are the variable names.
                    
        pow() function: it is a function in c that is comes in math.h header file which means is to calculate the fower of a number 
        syntax pow(number, power value) = pow(3.0, 2.0) means 3 to the power 2 

Integer and Float conversion:
    the result of two integer oprands is an integer value,  5 / 2 = 2
    same the result of two real constants is a real value,  5.0 / 2.0 = 2.5
    but the operation b/w an integer and real values always yields to real vallue 5 / 2.0 = 2.5

Hierarchy of operations: 

                it simply means the priority or precendence in which the operation is going to be performed.
                if i write 2 * 5 - 4 * 2 we dont know wheather its is 2(5-4(2)) or (2 * 5) - (4 * 2) so on so we use hierarchy to overcome this problem 

                Priority        Operatiors      Description
                  1st             * / %         Multiplication, division, and Modular division
                  2nd              + -          Addition and Substraction
                  3rd               =           Assignment 
        
        These are the hierarchy of the operators in this serial any equetion is going to solve.
        
